21/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A total of 45 people reportedly have been charged with involvement in the March assassination of Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic. 
The newspaper <I> Glas Javnosti </I> reported on Wednesday (20 August) that formal indictments have not yet been issued by the district court, and not all suspects are in custody. 
Among those still at large is Milorad "Legija" Lukovic, the infamous leader of the Zemun clan. 
(B92, Beta - 20/08/03)
